All Classes

  • All Classes Interface Summary Class Summary Enum Summary 
    Class Description
    Attempt
    Gathers the information for level Attempts from the server side to use in the client side.
    AttemptRepository
    Encapsulates the information for the viewmodels to display information needed for use in the applications.
    Cell
    Sets up the columns for the cells for maze generation.
    Direction
    Directions are enums set to allow the maze generator to know which direction is which.
    DungeonRunApplication
    Application class for the entire application.
    DungeonRunProxy
    This interface proxy will connect with the server and receive the incoming information for use on the client side.
    DungeonRunProxy.InstanceHolder
    Subclass in the proxy to hold instances of the proxy class.
    GameFragment
    Encapsulates the actual gameplay and displays for the UI.
    GameRepository
    The GameRepository encapsulates the needed methods to be gathered from the classes for Maze creation and allows the methods to be called upon when needed.
    GameViewModel
    Allows the viewModel for the game to be set up on the game screen.
    GoogleSignInService
    Encapsulates the Google sign in services needed to allow a user to sign in with their google account.
    LeaderboardAdapter
    Leaderboard adapter collects the information needed to display the database views for the recycler view in the leaderboard fragment.
    LeaderboardFragment
    Leaderboard encapsulates the information needed to display the leaderboard and stats.
    LeaderboardViewModel
    For the leaderboard to be set up and viewed in the application.
    LoginActivity
    Activity for logging in to Google sign in services.
    MainActivity
    Main activity creates the set up for screens to display and interact for UI experience.
    MainViewModel
    The viewmodel to set up the main view of the UI for the application when launched.
    Maze
    Maze.java is for the actual maze generation after the paths have been carved.
    MazeView
    MazeView creates the maze to display in the UI.
    SettingsFragment
    Allows the users to access the settings menu.
    User
    User information to be associated with each user that access the application.
    UserRepository
    Encapsulates the User entity for use within the client application.
